The implementation of _closeInputConnectionIfNeeded:
```
void _closeInputConnectionIfNeeded() {
    if (_hasInputConnection) {
      _textInputConnection.close();
      _textInputConnection = null;
      _lastKnownRemoteTextEditingValue = null;
    }
  }
```

I believe this implementation is correct and this is what we need to do for closing the connection after the platform message is received. 

Shall I rename this method instead? Am I missing anything?

